Description: Fragment of oval handle, with gradual curve of an Ephesian pottery transport amphora. Clay near fine pink-buff; white inclusions. Rectangular stamp with Greek inscription.
Curator's comments: Petrie Diary 1884-5 (EES Archive XVII 47) p. 201, 35 Name Chares. Of the Nikandros group.
Bibliographic references: Villing et al 2013-2015 / Naukratis: Greeks in Egypt (ID.104)
